.DT
add_menu_alias
Disk World creator help
add_menu_alias

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_menu_alias -  This method allows you to add an alias to an item sold in the pub.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void add_menu_alias(mixed alias,
string actual)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^alias%^RESET%^ - the alias to add
%^BOLD%^alias%^RESET%^ - the real item that the alias refers to
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/shops/inherit/pub.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method allows you to add an alias to an item sold in the pub.  Many
aliases are added by default so you shouldn't have to use this too
often.  See the help on "set_no_standard_alias()" to see what aliases are
added automatically.
.EP

.SH Example 1
.SI 5
// Allow "buy lancre ale" instead of "buy Ale from Lancre"
add_menu_alias( "lancre ale", "Ale from Lancre" );
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
add_menu_aliases(), query_menu_aliases(), remove_menu_alias(), set_no_standard_alias()

.EP

